cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on addressing security risks in machine learning computations in untrusted infrastructure.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of cloud computing to store and process sensitive data.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a secure machine learning framework based on TensorFlow.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of building a secure TensorFlow system and proposes a solution.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a hardware-assisted approach using Trusted Execution Environments (TEEs) to enable secure execution of machine learning computations.
